### ALGORITHM ###

Step 1: Start the program.
Step 2: Create a tuple with the values (10, 20, 30, 40, 20, 50) and print it.
Step 3: Calculate and print the total number of elements in the tuple using len().
Step 4: Count and print how many times the value 20 appears using count().
Step 5: Find and print the index position of the first occurrence of the value 30 using index().
Step 6: Calculate and print the maximum value, minimum value, and the sum of all elements in the tuple.
Step 7: Sort the elements in ascending order using sorted() and print the resulting list.
Step 8: Create a separate list [100, 200, 300], convert it into a tuple using tuple(), and print it.
Step 9: Create a tuple with boolean/integer values (0, False, 1).
Step 10: Use any() to check if at least one element is True, and all() to check if every element is True, then print both results.
Step 11: Stop the program.



